## Spacing Tokens (8px Grid)

Use token names — never pixel values.

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `xxs` | 4px | Icon-to-text, tight gaps |
| `xs` | 8px | Related items, list items |
| `sm` | 16px | Form fields, compact sections |
| `md` | 24px | Between sections |
| `lg` | 32px | Card padding, major gaps |
| `xl` | 40px | Page margins |

## Color Props

Use component color props — never hex values.

| Purpose | Prop |
|---------|------|
| Primary text | `color="default"` |
| Secondary text | `color="light"` |
| Primary action | `variant="primary"` |
| Success | `variant="success"` |
| Warning | `variant="warning"` |
| Error | `variant="error"` |
| Info | `variant="info"` |

## Styling — Priority Order

**Never use `style={{}}` directly on Playbook components.** Follow this priority:

1. **Playbook props first** — spacing tokens, color props, layout props
2. **Global props** — `maxWidth`, `width`, `height`, `minWidth`, `maxHeight`, `flex`, `flexGrow`
3. **`htmlOptions`** — for CSS that has no Playbook prop equivalent: `htmlOptions={{ style: { ... } }}`
4. **`className`** — only for non-Playbook concerns (animations, third-party integrations)

```tsx
// CORRECT — Playbook global props for dimensions (props in A-Z order)
<Card margin="auto" maxWidth="lg" padding="none">
<Card flex="3">
<Flex width="100%">

// CORRECT — htmlOptions when no global prop exists
<Flex htmlOptions={{ style: { height: "100vh" } }}>

// FORBIDDEN — never use style={{}} directly
<Flex style={{ width: "960px" }}>       // → maxWidth="lg" margin="auto"
<Card style={{ width: "540px" }}>       // → flex="3" (global prop on Card)
<Card style={{ padding: "24px" }}>      // → padding="md"
<Body style={{ color: "#687887" }}>     // → color="light"
```

### ERB Styling (`pb_rails`)

In ERB, `html_options` is a key **inside** the `props:` hash — NOT a separate keyword argument.

```erb
<%# CORRECT — html_options inside props hash %>
<%= pb_rails("flex", props: {
  orientation: "column",
  html_options: { style: "background: rgba(193,205,214,0.1)" }
}) %>

<%# CORRECT — hash syntax for style (also valid) %>
<%= pb_rails("card", props: {
  padding: "none",
  html_options: { style: { width: "fit-content" } }
}) %>

<%# WRONG — html_options as separate keyword (raises "unknown keyword" error) %>
<%= pb_rails("flex", props: { orientation: "column" }, html_options: { style: "..." }) %>
```

### Centered Content Pattern

For centered, width-constrained page content (common in Nitro forms):

```tsx
// CORRECT — Card with maxWidth + margin="auto"
<Card align="center" margin="auto" maxWidth="lg" padding="none">
  <Flex align="stretch" gap="md" padding="md" width="100%">
    <FlexItem flex="3">{/* main content */}</FlexItem>
    <FlexItem flex="2">{/* sidebar */}</FlexItem>
  </Flex>
</Card>

// WRONG — inline styles for width and centering
<Flex style={{ width: "960px", margin: "0 auto" }}>
```

### Column Proportions

Use the `flex` global prop for proportional sizing instead of fixed pixel widths.
Apply `flex` directly to any child component — `FlexItem` is NOT required.

| Figma Proportion | `flex` global prop |
|------------------|-------------------|
| 60% / 40% | `flex="3"` / `flex="2"` |
| 75% / 25% | `flex="3"` / `flex="1"` |
| 50% / 50% | `flex="1"` / `flex="1"` |
| 70% / 30% | `flex="7"` / `flex="3"` |

